        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2017-12-06 19:06:04.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nA quick thought or two starting out...  This should eventually get a proc switch to enable/disabled it, and I'll let others weigh in, but I would think we'd want to default to building it.  It could be off by default.\n\nAlso, given that the kernel version of LZ4 varies a lot, I would personally be happier if we just used our own all the time.  I know that's bad, etc, etc, but a lot of the kernels we currently support have some pretty out of date versions of LZ4, I think.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "1dc19069f72559289dcf832ddb33fc853320b437",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 302,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "paf@cray.com",
        "username": "paf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2017-12-06 19:59:37.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nGot an -ENOMEM in osc_build_rpc, specifically from prep_req, then panicked immediately.\n\ncmp pool logged that it successfully finished the alloc.  BTW, that should be something friendly than CERROR.  CDEBUG(D_INFO, perhaps, or maybe the compression code could get its own mask entry.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
