          "tz": 60
        },
        "subject": "LU-10026: WIP: client-side compression (write path)",
        "message": "LU-10026: WIP: client-side compression (write path)\n\nData is compressed by the client and decompressed by the server.\n\nThis also adds build system changes for compression:\n- The configure parameter --enable-compression can be used to enable compression.\n- If lz4 is not available in the kernel (< 3.11), we build a private module for it.\n\nChange-Id: I0b92fb9759cda6c0c182ca9c4d5a72cb9e159c4b\nTest-Parameters: forbuildonly\nSigned-off-by: Anna Fuchs <anna.fuchs@informatik.uni-hamburg.de>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
